<h3>1.5.  Related Systems</h3>
<p>
   Systems that provide functionality comparable to the Test Tool include
   <ul>
      <li><a href="http://www.webassign.net/">WebAssign</a></li>
      <li><a href="http://www.testshop.com">TestGenerator</a></li>
      <li><a href="http://www.easytestmaker.com/">Easy Test Maker</a></li>
      <li><a href="http://www.exambuilder.com">ExamBuilder</a></li>
      <li><a href="http://www.blackboard.com">Blackboard.com</a></li>
      <li><a href="http://www.hirtlesoftware.com/p_rtgpro.htm">Random Test Generator PRO</a></li>
   </ul>
</p>

<p>
   Each of these systems provides a wide variety of test-making and test-taking
functionality.  In terms of such functionality, the goal for the Test Tool
is to provide features that make online test taking more like test-taking
in a classroom environment as well as features that make on and offline test
creation simple. The Test Tool does provide modest functional improvements
in three areas, when compared to most commercially available tools. These
improvements are:
</p>

<ol type=a>
   <li>more flexibility in question types, specifically, programming
   questions</li>
   <li>more options for test taking, including printed paper tests</li>
   <li>more options for generating tests from previous questions</li>
</ol>

<p>
   The goals for the Test Tool relating to public domain source code and sound
   pedagogical development are not met by any of the above commercial systems.
</p>
